    "text": "Last night's three drinks are the most likely story here, and nothing suggests something is wrong with you. Recovery is 48%, well below your 7-day average of 67%. The contributors point the same way: your resting heart rate of 63 bpm is about 6 beats over your 30-day baseline of 56.9 bpm, and your HRV of 49 ms is well below its 30-day baseline of 58.3 ms — alcohol evenings often line up with exactly this overnight signature. It reads like a one-night hit, not illness. The lever for tonight: skip the drinks, hydrate through the afternoon, and get to bed at your usual time — this pattern typically rebounds within a night or two.",
